22/03/2011
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Hundreds of people organised via Facebook gathered on Monday (March 21st) outside parliament in Podgorica to protest the country's economic situation.
They demanded better living standards, more jobs, and decent pensions.
Also at the rally were representatives of the opposition Movement for Change, Socialist People's Party and the New Serb Democracy.
(RTCG, Pcnen, Radio Free Europe - 21/03/11)
